WEBVTT

00:00.542 --> 00:01.959
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i>
<i>"RED BAND SOCIETY"...</i>

00:02.041 --> 00:03.667
THIS COULD BE THE BREAKTHROUGH
CHARLIE NEEDS.

00:03.750 --> 00:06.333
SO YOU'RE PROPOSING WE BRING
NADAY HERE TO EXAMINE HIM.

00:06.417 --> 00:07.959
WHAT'S THE BIG DEAL
IF NADAY COMES?

00:08.041 --> 00:09.083
WHY ARE YOU
SO AGAINST IT?

00:09.166 --> 00:10.875
BECAUSE IT IS A WASTE OF TIME
AND RESOURCES.

00:10.959 --> 00:12.375
IS THAT IT?

00:12.458 --> 00:13.750
OR IS IT THAT YOU DON'T WANT
ANOTHER DOCTOR HERE

00:13.834 --> 00:15.166
THAT CAN DO IN ONE DAY

00:15.250 --> 00:16.834
WHAT YOU HAVEN'T BEEN
ABLE TO DO IN MONTHS?

00:16.917 --> 00:18.542
THOSE USED TO BE MY FAVORITE
WHEN I WAS LITTLE.

00:18.625 --> 00:20.375
CAN I HAVE ONE?
HELP YOURSELF.

00:21.542 --> 00:23.083
WHAT HAPPENS IF THEY CAN'T
FIND YOU ANOTHER LIVER?

00:23.166 --> 00:25.208
SAME THING
THAT HAPPENS TO YOU.

00:25.291 --> 00:27.208
[ COUGHS ]
DASH, TAKE IT EASY. BREATHE.

00:27.291 --> 00:28.375
[ COUGHS, SPITS ]

00:28.458 --> 00:29.792
OH, MY GOD!
OKAY, OKAY.

00:29.875 --> 00:31.667
Leo: DASH!
HEY, NURSE, WE NEED A GURNEY.

00:31.750 --> 00:32.959
CHARLIE?

00:37.041 --> 00:41.041
CHARLIE?
ARE YOU IN THERE?

00:41.125 --> 00:42.166
SAY SOMETHING, BABY.

00:42.250 --> 00:45.291
Charlie: <i>I ONCE SAW A POSTER IN</i>
<i>MY DENTIST'S OFFICE THAT SAID,</i>

00:45.375 --> 00:49.792
<i>"YOU CAN'T ALWAYS CONTROL</i>
<i>WHAT GOES ON OUTSIDE..."</i>

00:49.875 --> 00:53.166
ARE YOU IN THERE, BABY?
SAY SOMETHING.

00:54.583 --> 00:57.333
[ Chuckling ]
YOU'RE AWAKE.

00:57.417 --> 00:59.333
HE'S AWAKE!

00:59.417 --> 01:02.208
<i>"...BUT YOU</i> CAN <i>ALWAYS CONTROL</i>
<i>WHAT GOES ON INSIDE."</i>

01:02.291 --> 01:04.208
SOMEBODY PAGE DR. McANDREW!
[ LAUGHS ]

01:04.291 --> 01:06.000
WHAT?
DID YOU HAVE A STROKE?

01:06.083 --> 01:07.959
CHARLIE'S AWAKE.
WHAT?!

01:08.041 --> 01:09.291
OH, MY GOD!

01:09.375 --> 01:11.000
LOOK AT THOSE EYES.

01:11.083 --> 01:13.333
ALL THE FARTING, THOUGH, KID.

01:13.417 --> 01:15.667
Leo: HEY, WHAT'S GOING ON?
CHARLIE'S AWAKE.

01:15.750 --> 01:17.333
LOOK, HIS EYES ARE OPEN.

01:17.417 --> 01:19.000
NO WAY!
YOU'RE KIDDING.

01:19.083 --> 01:20.542
[ GASPS ]
Jackson: GET McANDREW!

01:20.625 --> 01:22.000
HEY, CHARLIE.
OH, MY GOD.

01:22.083 --> 01:23.333
<i>HI TO YOU, TOO.</i>

01:23.417 --> 01:25.000
THAT'S AMAZING.

01:25.083 --> 01:26.333
I WISHED ON LIKE 46 EYELASHES
FOR THIS TO HAPPEN.

01:26.417 --> 01:29.333
YOU GUYS,
I'M SO EXCITED!

01:29.417 --> 01:31.667
[ LAUGHTER ]
[ WHISTLES ]

01:31.750 --> 01:34.500
GUYS, I HATE TO BE A BUZZKILL,
BUT HE'S NOT MOVING OR TALKING.

01:34.583 --> 01:36.542
WHY ARE WE CELEBRATING?

01:36.625 --> 01:38.250
WE'RE CELEBRATING
BECAUSE AWAKE IS ENOUGH

01:38.333 --> 01:39.709
TO KEEP HIM
FROM BEING TRANSFERRED

01:39.792 --> 01:41.709
OUT OF OCEAN PARK HOSPITAL.

01:41.792 --> 01:42.875
Kara: SERIOUSLY?

01:42.959 --> 01:44.750
YES.
YEP! [ CHUCKLES ]

01:44.834 --> 01:46.959
[ LAUGHS ] WOW.
Kara: WAIT.

01:47.041 --> 01:48.583
SO, DOES THIS MEAN I DON'T
KISS HIM OFF?
Emma: OKAY, NOT THE TIME.

01:48.667 --> 01:50.000
Jackson: CHARLIE, THIS IS --
THIS IS NURSE JACKSON.

01:50.083 --> 01:53.500
<i>LOOKS LIKE</i>
<i>MR. "WE ALL DIE ALONE"</i>

01:53.583 --> 01:56.041
<i>IS ALSO HAVING</i>
<i>SOME ISSUES WITH CONTROL.</i>

01:56.125 --> 01:57.834
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

01:57.917 --> 01:59.333
IT'S STILL ME.

01:59.417 --> 02:00.917
Jackson: HEY, CHARLIE!

02:08.500 --> 02:10.750
HAVE YOU PEOPLE NEVER HEARD
OF BOUNDARIES, MAN?

02:10.834 --> 02:12.375
CHARLIE'S AWAKE.

02:12.458 --> 02:13.750
WHAT?

02:13.834 --> 02:15.000
Jordi: YEAH,
AND NURSE JACKSON'S BACK.

02:15.083 --> 02:16.709
THEY LIFTED
HER SUSPENSION.

02:16.792 --> 02:19.417
NURSE JACKSON, CHARLIE,
AND YOUR HAIR'S GROWING BACK?

02:19.500 --> 02:21.125
YO, HOW LONG
HAVE I BEEN ASLEEP, MAN?

02:21.208 --> 02:23.083
CHARLIE'S EYES ARE OPEN,
BUT HE CAN'T MOVE OR TALK.

02:23.166 --> 02:25.083
WE WANT TO GET CHARLIE SOMETHING
FUN TO LOOK AT, YOU KNOW?

02:25.166 --> 02:26.917
WE'RE THINKING THAT IF WE CAN
LIFT HIS SPIRITS ENOUGH,

02:27.000 --> 02:29.417
MAYBE IT'LL INSPIRE HIM
TO TALK TO US.

02:29.500 --> 02:32.083
GOT ANY IDEAS?
HELL, THAT'S A NO-BRAINER.

02:32.166 --> 02:34.250
ALL RIGHT, LET ME REPHRASE
THE QUESTION.

02:34.333 --> 02:37.542
WHAT IS ONE THING THAT A FUTURE
BALLER LIKE CHARLIE WOULD LIKE?

02:37.625 --> 02:38.709
BOOBS.
BOOBS.

02:38.792 --> 02:40.750
BINGO.
YOU'RE KIDDING, RIGHT?

02:40.834 --> 02:42.125
[ SCOFFS ]
I MEAN, COME ON, GUYS.

02:42.208 --> 02:43.583
I THINK WE CAN AIM
A LITTLE HIGHER, HERE --

02:43.667 --> 02:45.583
MAYBE SOMETHING
MORE INSPIRATIONAL.

02:45.667 --> 02:47.625
YEAH, SHE'S RIGHT --
UH, I THINK WE NEED TO COME UP

02:47.709 --> 02:49.792
WITH A FEW THINGS
THAT WE KNOW CHARLIE LIKES.

02:49.875 --> 02:51.291
KARA SAID
HE LIKES PIZZA.

02:51.375 --> 02:52.500
THERE'S NOTHING FUN
ABOUT SEEING PIZZA.

02:52.583 --> 02:54.375
YOU KNOW,
EATING PIZZA, MAYBE.

02:54.458 --> 02:56.625
WHAT ABOUT THOSE LITTLE ORIGAMI
CREATURES HE HAS IN HIS ROOM?

02:56.709 --> 02:58.417
WE COULD MAKE A BUNCH MORE

02:58.500 --> 03:00.834
AND THEN STRING UP A GIANT
ORIGAMI MOBILE OVER HIS BED.

03:00.917 --> 03:04.166
WHY WOULD WE DO THAT WHEN
MY FIRST IDEA WAS WAY BETTER?

03:04.250 --> 03:06.458
MOBILES STIMULATE
NEURAL ACTIVITY IN NEWBORNS.

03:06.542 --> 03:07.709
KNOW WHAT ELSE
NEWBORNS LIKE?

03:08.667 --> 03:11.083
BREASTFEEDING.
YOU KNOW WHY?

03:11.166 --> 03:12.250
BOOBS.

03:12.333 --> 03:13.959
[ LAUGHTER ]

03:14.041 --> 03:15.709
HEY,
WHAT ABOUT A PUPPY?

03:15.792 --> 03:17.959
I'M NOT SAYING IT'LL DO, LIKE,
THE NEURAL THINGS OR WHATEVER.

03:18.041 --> 03:19.709
BUT LAST WEEK,
WHEN I WAS IN CHEMO,

03:19.792 --> 03:23.125
THAT WEIRD PET-THERAPY LADY
CAME IN WITH A BLACK LAB PUPPY.

03:23.208 --> 03:24.458
IT WAS PRETTY COOL.

03:24.542 --> 03:27.500
I SAY WE GET IT ALL.
WHY NOT?

03:27.583 --> 03:30.333
CHARLIE'S ONE OF US.
HE'S THE ORIGINAL RED BANDER.

03:30.417 --> 03:32.667
AND HE WAS THERE FOR US
WHEN WE NEEDED HIM,

03:32.750 --> 03:34.834
SO WHY DON'T WE HELP HIM?

03:34.917 --> 03:36.417
LET'S PUT
OUR MONEY TOGETHER

03:36.500 --> 03:38.625
AND DO WHATEVER IT TAKES,
YOU KNOW, FOR CHARLIE.

03:40.583 --> 03:42.000
FOR CHARLIE.

03:42.083 --> 03:46.083
<i>I, FOR ONE,</i>
<i>AM LOVING THIS PLAN!</i>

03:51.333 --> 03:53.083
WILL YOU JUST PICK SOMETHING
ALREADY?

03:53.166 --> 03:54.250
I DON'T HAVE FOREVER.

03:54.333 --> 03:56.417
THIS IS
A SERIOUS DECISION.

03:56.500 --> 03:59.208
A SNACK DETERMINES YOUR MOOD
FOR THE REST OF THE DAY.

03:59.291 --> 04:01.333
OH. WELL, IN THAT CASE,
TAKE YOUR TIME.

04:01.417 --> 04:03.166
I DON'T WANT TO
FIND YOU CRYING

04:03.250 --> 04:04.959
OVER YOUR CANDY WRAPPERS
LATER.

04:05.041 --> 04:09.291
YOU'RE THE BEST TERRIBLE PERSON
I'VE MET IN A LONG TIME.

04:09.375 --> 04:10.834
I MEAN, YOU REALLY
THROW YOURSELF INTO IT.

04:10.917 --> 04:12.667
THANK YOU.

04:12.750 --> 04:15.959
I'VE ALREADY LEARNED SO MUCH
FROM WATCHING YOU.

04:16.041 --> 04:17.333
I NOTICED YOU LEFT

04:17.417 --> 04:19.166
THE FESTIVITIES EARLY
LAST NIGHT, TOO.

04:19.250 --> 04:23.375
YEAH, WELL, I HAD REACHED MY
NATURAL TOLERANCE FOR HAPPINESS.

04:23.458 --> 04:25.041
TOO REAL FOR YOU?

04:25.125 --> 04:27.208
PLEASE.
I'M THE EPITOME OF REAL.

04:27.291 --> 04:30.166
REAL AND UNCENSORED
AREN'T EXACTLY THE SAME THING.

04:30.250 --> 04:31.542
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:31.625 --> 04:33.542
[ ASHLEY CLEARS THROAT ]

04:33.625 --> 04:35.375
[ CHUCKLES ]
NO WAY.

04:35.458 --> 04:36.875
HI!
HI!

04:36.959 --> 04:38.709
OH!

04:38.792 --> 04:40.208
OH, I MISSED YOU.

04:40.291 --> 04:41.834
MISSED YOU.

04:41.917 --> 04:43.500
HOW ARE YOU?
DOING WELL. HOW ARE YOU?

04:43.583 --> 04:46.041
YOU LOOK AMAZING.
THANK YOU.

04:50.959 --> 04:54.083
UH, CHARLIE, I NEED YOU TO BLINK
IF YOU CAN HEAR ME.

04:55.208 --> 04:56.834
[ GASPS ]
THAT'S GREAT.

04:56.917 --> 05:01.291
UH, HOW ABOUT YOU BLINK TWICE
IF YOU LIKE MY TIE.

05:03.000 --> 05:04.417
[ LAUGHTER ]

05:04.500 --> 05:06.250
STILL HAS
HIS SENSE OF HUMOR.

05:06.333 --> 05:07.750
<i>I'M HERE ALL WEEK, FOLKS.</i>

05:07.834 --> 05:09.625
<i>DON'T FORGET TO TIP</i>
<i>YOUR NURSES.</i>

05:09.709 --> 05:11.375
OH, THIS REMINDS ME OF THAT
ARTSY MOVIE I SAW BY ACCIDENT,

05:11.458 --> 05:13.041
"THE DIVING BELL
AND THE BUTTERFLY,"

05:13.125 --> 05:15.250
WITH THE -- THE GUY WHO COULD
TALK WITH THE --

05:15.333 --> 05:16.750
HE -- THAT'S HOW HE TALKS.
HE BLINKS.

05:16.834 --> 05:19.083
HOW DO YOU SEE A MOVIE
BY ACCIDENT?

05:19.166 --> 05:20.583
WELL, I THOUGHT IT WAS
THE SEQUEL

05:20.667 --> 05:22.250
TO ASHTON KUTCHER'S
"BUTTERFLY EFFECT."

05:22.333 --> 05:23.917
[ CHUCKLES ]
OKEYDOKEY.

05:24.000 --> 05:26.417
ALTHOUGH I THINK EYELID GUY
WAS SUFFERING

05:26.500 --> 05:27.875
FROM LOCKED-IN SYNDROME

05:27.959 --> 05:30.250
CAUSED BY DAMAGE
TO THE LOWER CRANIAL AREA,

05:30.333 --> 05:31.542
WHICH IS NOT
PRESENTING IN THIS --
YEAH, IT'S NOT PRESENTING
IN THIS --

05:31.625 --> 05:33.083
[ Laughing ]
SORRY, GO AHEAD.

05:33.166 --> 05:34.208
NO, YOU GO.

05:34.291 --> 05:36.000
IT'S ALL GOOD.
I GET IT.

05:36.083 --> 05:38.291
OKAY, CHARLIE, GIVE MY HAND
A BIG SQUEEZE IF YOU CAN.

05:38.375 --> 05:40.458
<i>DUDE, I HAVEN'T MOVED</i>
<i>IN TWO MONTHS.</i>

05:40.542 --> 05:42.625
LOOKS LIKE MOTOR SKILLS
ARE DORMANT.

05:42.709 --> 05:45.291
YEAH, BUT HE'S FULLY RESPONSIVE,
WHICH IS EXCELLENT NEWS.

05:45.375 --> 05:46.959
I WANT TO GET
A FULL NEURO EXAM.

05:47.041 --> 05:48.250
UH, WHO'S THE NEUROLOGIST
ON CALL TODAY?

05:48.333 --> 05:50.917
DR. NADAY.
MM!

05:51.000 --> 05:52.291
NO, ACTUALLY,
IT'S DR. KLEIN.

05:52.375 --> 05:54.041
NO, NO, NO.

05:54.125 --> 05:55.667
WHAT SHE MEANS IS DR. NADAY
IS SUPPOSED TO ARRIVE TOMORROW,

05:55.750 --> 05:58.750
AND HE'S ONE OF THE FOREMOST
NEUROLOGISTS IN THE WORLD,

05:58.834 --> 06:01.250
AND HE'S COMING SPECIFICALLY
TO EXAMINE CHARLIE.

06:01.333 --> 06:03.250
IT'S SERENDIPITOUS.

06:03.333 --> 06:04.583
Brittany:
THAT'S GREAT. GREAT.

06:04.667 --> 06:06.291
ONLY THE BEST
FOR OUR LITTLE MAN.

06:06.375 --> 06:08.542
MAYBE YOU WANT TO HOLD OFF
ON RUNNING SOME OF THOSE TESTS,

06:08.625 --> 06:10.834
JUST DO YOU DON'T
RUFFLE HIS FEATHERS.

06:12.333 --> 06:14.583
I DO NOT CARE ABOUT
RUFFLING HIS FEATHERS.

06:14.667 --> 06:16.500
I'VE BEEN WAITING FOR CHARLIE
TO WAKE UP

06:16.583 --> 06:18.166
FOR A COUPLE MONTHS NOW, AND
I'M NOT GONNA WAIT ANY LONGER.

06:18.250 --> 06:20.166
I WILL BE HAPPY
TO GO OVER THE TEST RESULTS

06:20.250 --> 06:21.917
WITH NADAY
WHEN HE GETS HERE.

06:22.000 --> 06:23.500
LET'S GET A NEW MRI TO SEE
IF THE SWELLING WENT DOWN.

06:23.583 --> 06:25.208
ALSO, I'LL NEED KLEIN
TO RUN A FULL BATTERY,

06:25.291 --> 06:28.333
SO CRANIAL NERVES, UH,
REFLEXIVE ASSESSMENT, E.E.G.

06:28.417 --> 06:31.709
AND DO NOT FORGET TO PAGE ME
WHEN HIS PARENTS ARRIVE.

06:33.250 --> 06:34.792
HE'S AWAKE!
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

06:34.875 --> 06:36.583
LAST TIME, I PROMISE.

06:42.208 --> 06:44.208
♪ UNH, UNH, UNH ♪

06:44.291 --> 06:46.083
♪ I DREAMED OF BEING RICH
AND FAMOUS ♪

06:46.166 --> 06:47.709
Leo: SO, NURSE JACKSON
GAVE US THE OKAY

06:47.792 --> 06:49.375
TO HEAD OFF CAMPUS
FOR A BIT.

06:49.458 --> 06:51.709
UH, JORDI, IS IT COOL
IF WE USE YOUR NEW CAR?

06:51.792 --> 06:54.125
SURE.

06:54.208 --> 06:55.583
♪ I AIN'T HAVE MONEY
FOR TUITION ♪

06:55.667 --> 06:57.792
HEY, IS THE CHEMO
KICKING YOUR ASS TODAY?

06:57.875 --> 07:00.417
IT ALWAYS SEEMS TO ROLL THROUGH
WHEN YOU LEAST EXPECT IT.

07:00.500 --> 07:03.291
NO, I ACTUALLY FEEL
PRETTY SOLID RIGHT NOW.

07:03.375 --> 07:05.458
OKAY. GREAT.
UM, EMMA'S DOWNSTAIRS.

07:05.542 --> 07:07.667
I'M GONNA GO GRAB MY LEG.
I'LL MEET YOU OUTSIDE.

07:07.750 --> 07:10.166
♪ UNH, UNH, OKAY ♪

07:10.250 --> 07:13.000
MAYBE YOU GUYS SHOULD JUST
GO WITHOUT ME.

07:13.083 --> 07:14.792
THE WHOLE LEO-AND-EMMA THING --
IT'S STILL A LITTLE MUCH.

07:14.875 --> 07:17.750
YEAH, WHAT'S UP? YOU NEVER BEEN
REJECTED BY A WOMAN BEFORE?

07:17.834 --> 07:19.083
♪ WITH MY OLDER BROTHER ♪
♪ YEAH ♪

07:19.166 --> 07:21.458
ONE OTHER TIME.

07:21.542 --> 07:23.375
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

07:35.208 --> 07:36.792
LET'S JUST SAY
I DIDN'T HANDLE IT WELL.

07:36.875 --> 07:38.750
YEAH, BUT THIS ISN'T ABOUT
BEING REJECTED.

07:38.834 --> 07:40.208
SO, THEN,
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

07:40.291 --> 07:41.166
I THOUGHT YOU AND LEO
HAD WORKED IT OUT.

07:41.250 --> 07:42.917
WE DID.

07:43.000 --> 07:45.291
BUT EMMA AND I HAVEN'T SAID
TWO WORDS TO EACH OTHER

07:45.375 --> 07:46.542
SINCE THAT NIGHT
ON THE ROOF.

07:46.625 --> 07:47.959
OH,
YOU MEAN WHEN YOU SAID

07:48.041 --> 07:49.667
YOU WANTED YOUR FEELINGS
TO FEEL THINGS?

07:49.750 --> 07:51.125
[ SCOFFS ]

07:51.208 --> 07:52.875
DUDE, I'M THE EYES AND EARS
OF THIS PLACE,

07:52.959 --> 07:54.709
AND...
I WAS ON THE ROOF.

07:54.792 --> 07:56.375
I JUST DON'T KNOW HOW TO BE
AROUND HER.

07:56.458 --> 07:57.834
JUST ACT COOL, FOOL.

07:57.917 --> 07:59.667
JUST ACT LIKE
NOTHING EVER HAPPENED,

07:59.750 --> 08:02.667
AND YOU'LL EASE RIGHT BACK
INTO THE FRIEND ZONE.

08:02.750 --> 08:04.500
WE NEVER LEFT
THE FRIEND ZONE.

08:04.583 --> 08:07.166
♪ DAMN NEAR THE ONLY THING
THAT HELPED THE PAIN ♪

08:07.250 --> 08:10.333
SO, HE'S AWAKE,
AND HE CAN HEAR US.

08:10.417 --> 08:11.834
ARE YOU SURE?
YES, YES.

08:11.917 --> 08:13.291
WE'RE DOING
SOME MORE TESTS,

08:13.375 --> 08:15.083
SO WE SHOULD KNOW MORE
IN A FEW DAYS.

08:15.166 --> 08:17.250
BUT HE HAS HAD
MODERATE IMPROVEMENT

08:17.333 --> 08:18.959
IN HIS BRAIN-WAVE
PATTERN.

08:19.041 --> 08:20.458
CHARLIE'S CONDITION
IS PRESENTING

08:20.542 --> 08:23.166
AS EXPRESSIVE APHASIA.
I DON'T CARE.

08:23.250 --> 08:25.166
HE'S AWAKE.
THAT'S ALL I CARE ABOUT.

08:25.250 --> 08:26.834
SO, HOW LONG
UNTIL HE TALKS AGAIN?

08:26.917 --> 08:28.834
IT'S HARD TO GUESS
UNTIL WE HAVE MORE SPECIFICS.

08:28.917 --> 08:31.834
IT COULD BE AN HOUR, A DAY,
A WEEK, A MONTH.

08:31.917 --> 08:34.333
OR MAYBE NEVER.

08:34.417 --> 08:36.875
SIR, I'M SORRY, UH, CAN I --
CAN I HELP YOU WITH SOMETHING?

08:36.959 --> 08:38.709
NOT UNLESS YOU'RE
DR. ERIN GRACE.

08:38.792 --> 08:40.625
SHE WAS THE ONE
THAT CALLED ME

08:40.709 --> 08:42.041
AND ASKED ME TO COME HERE AND
CHECK ON A PATIENT OF YOURS --

08:42.125 --> 08:44.875
CHARLIE HUTCHISON,
LITTLE COMA DUDE.

08:46.959 --> 08:48.542
YOU'RE
DR. LAWRENCE NADAY?

08:48.625 --> 08:50.250
LAST I CHECKED.

08:50.333 --> 08:54.000
WOW. YOU LOOK DIFFERENT
FROM YOUR TED TALK VIDEOS.

08:54.083 --> 08:55.709
THANK YOU FOR NOTICING.
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

08:55.792 --> 08:58.500
YEAH, I RECENTLY DROPPED A FEW
POUNDS ON THIS CAVEMAN DIET.

08:58.583 --> 09:01.959
IT'S A STRICT REGIMEN OF BUFFALO
SHANK AND ALMOND-FLOUR PIZZA.

09:02.041 --> 09:03.250
IT'S VERY EFFECTIVE.

09:03.333 --> 09:05.583
Does back you up,
though.

09:05.667 --> 09:07.500
DR. NADAY, HI.
I'M DR. GRACE.

09:07.583 --> 09:09.000
OH!
WE SPOKE ON THE PHONE.

09:09.083 --> 09:10.625
YOU ARE THE REASON I AM HERE!
THAT'S --

09:10.709 --> 09:12.291
HI.
OH. [ CHUCKLES ]
HIT ME.

09:12.375 --> 09:14.417
[ LAUGHS ] COME HERE.
[ GROWLS, LAUGHS ]

09:14.500 --> 09:16.750
YOU CAN CALL ME "LARRY."

09:16.834 --> 09:18.083
CALL ME LARRY!
OKAY, LARRY.

09:18.166 --> 09:19.583
SAY, "LET GO, LARRY."
LET GO, LARRY.

09:19.667 --> 09:21.250
YOU DID IT.
OKAY, PUT ME DOWN.
THANK YOU.

09:21.333 --> 09:22.709
GREAT.

09:27.625 --> 09:29.709
YOU LOOK LIKE A SAD,
LITTLE TURTLE EMOTICON.

09:29.792 --> 09:31.166
WHAT'S WRONG?

09:31.250 --> 09:32.500
DID YOU KNOW HUNTER HAD
A GIRLFRIEND?

09:32.583 --> 09:34.291
NO, BUT I DON'T KNOW
A LOT OF THINGS.

09:34.375 --> 09:36.125
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW DR. McANDREW
HAD AN EX-GIRLFRIEND --

09:36.208 --> 09:38.875
WHO IS HERE, I MEAN --
WHO IS RIGHT HERE.

09:38.959 --> 09:40.792
OH, SO YOU DIDN'T NOTICE
HUNTER PARADING AROUND

09:40.875 --> 09:42.041
ON HIS BLOND AMBITION
TOUR?

09:42.125 --> 09:44.250
[ GASPS ]

09:44.333 --> 09:46.834
MY GOSH,
YOU LIKE HUNTER.

09:46.917 --> 09:50.834
UM, I'M AFFLICTED WITH
A VERY SERIOUS HEART CONDITION.

09:50.917 --> 09:53.500
I HAVE MUCH MORE IMPORTANT
THINGS TO WORRY ABOUT.

09:53.583 --> 09:55.625
I JUST THOUGHT
WE HAD A CONNECTION.

09:55.709 --> 09:58.458
SO...

09:58.542 --> 10:00.625
TELL HIM THAT.
SHH!

10:00.709 --> 10:02.625
MAYBE IT WILL BE ENOUGH
TO WIN HIM OVER.

10:02.709 --> 10:04.041
YOU MEAN, LIKE,
BE HONEST WITH HIM?

10:04.125 --> 10:05.792
[ SCOFFS ]
PLEASE. THAT NEVER WORKS.

10:05.875 --> 10:08.792
HOW I'D NORMALLY DO THIS IS BY
TEARING DOWN THAT OLD HAG.

10:08.875 --> 10:11.834
BEING SICK
HAS MADE ME LOSE MY GAME.

10:11.917 --> 10:16.500
TAKING WHAT I WANT, GETTING
MY WAY, IS MY SUPERPOWER.

10:16.583 --> 10:18.667
NOW THAT I HAVE TO BE NICE
TO GET A STUPID HEART,

10:18.750 --> 10:20.291
I'VE LOST ALL CONTROL.

10:20.375 --> 10:22.125
IT JUST COMPLETELY SUCKS.

10:22.208 --> 10:24.792
WELL, MAYBE YOU SHOULD TAKE
A PAGE FROM MY FAVORITE AUTHOR.

10:24.875 --> 10:26.458
<i>WAIT FOR IT.</i>

10:26.542 --> 10:29.000
OPRAH SAYS IF THERE'S NOTHING
YOU CAN DO, DO NOTHING.

10:29.083 --> 10:31.333
OKAY, OPRAH ISN'T TECHNICALLY
AN AUTHOR.

10:31.417 --> 10:32.667
IT'S CALLED MINDFULNESS.

10:32.750 --> 10:34.125
THE MORE YOU PRACTICE
DOING NOTHING,

10:34.208 --> 10:35.500
THE MORE THE UNIVERSE
EVENTUALLY REWARDS YOU.

10:35.583 --> 10:36.959
WE COULD DO IT
TOGETHER!

10:37.041 --> 10:38.500
[ Sarcastically ]
FUNSIES.

10:38.583 --> 10:40.166
THAT'S NO WAY
TO SAY "FUNSIES."

10:40.250 --> 10:42.041
WHAT DO YOU HAVE TO LOSE
BY TRYING?

10:42.125 --> 10:44.542
ASIDE FROM EVERYTHING
THAT MAKES ME COOL?

10:44.625 --> 10:46.458
Ashley:
WE SHOULD GO SOMETIME.

10:46.542 --> 10:48.333
I'D LOVE TO.
WE CAN DO WHATEVER.

10:48.417 --> 10:50.667
NOTHING.

10:50.750 --> 10:52.834
COME ON.

10:52.917 --> 10:54.834
DID YOU HEAR ME
PLAYING GUITAR?

10:54.917 --> 10:56.542
DID YOU FEEL ME
BRUSHING YOUR HAIR?

10:56.625 --> 10:57.875
DID YOU ENJOY THE GRAPHIC NOVEL
THAT I READ TO YOU

10:57.959 --> 10:59.667
ABOUT THE NINJA
AND THE ANDROID COP?

10:59.750 --> 11:01.375
DID I PICK OUT THE RIGHT COLORS
FOR YOUR NEW PAJAMAS?

11:01.458 --> 11:03.166
HOLD ON A SECOND. HE HASN'T
ANSWERED MY LAST QUESTION YET.

11:03.250 --> 11:04.375
YOU'VE BEEN INTERROGATING HIM
LIKE A WAR CORRESPONDENT

11:04.458 --> 11:05.834
ALL MORNING.

11:05.917 --> 11:06.709
WHOA, PEOPLE, PEOPLE, PEOPLE,
COME ON.

11:06.792 --> 11:08.250
TAKE A CHILL PILL.

11:08.333 --> 11:10.083
HE'S NOT A CELLPHONE
YOU PASS BACK AND FORTH.

11:10.166 --> 11:11.917
<i>THANK YOU. I'M EXHAUSTED.</i>

11:12.000 --> 11:13.291
WHAT'S HAPPENING.

11:13.375 --> 11:16.041
OH, MY GOD, CHARLIE?
WE'RE LOSING HIM.

11:16.125 --> 11:18.041
<i>NO REST FOR THE WEARY.</i>

11:18.125 --> 11:22.208
EASY, EASY.
YOU HAVE A NORMAL SON IN THERE.

11:22.291 --> 11:24.041
WE JUST HAVE TO FIND A WAY
TO GET HIM OUT.

11:24.125 --> 11:25.917
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

11:26.000 --> 11:27.250
NICK, MANDY, MAY I HAVE A MOMENT
ALONE WITH DR. NADAY, PLEASE?

11:27.333 --> 11:30.583
YEAH. WE'LL BE RIGHT BACK,
CHARLIE.

11:30.667 --> 11:32.583
THANKS.

11:32.667 --> 11:35.166
DENA, YOU HAVE
A REAL ENERGY ABOUT YOU.

11:35.250 --> 11:36.667
HAS ANYONE
EVER TOLD YOU THAT?

11:36.750 --> 11:37.959
EVERY DAY.

11:38.041 --> 11:39.709
THIS IS CHARLIE'S
PATIENT HISTORY.

11:39.792 --> 11:42.166
I'D BE HAPPY TO BRING YOU
UP TO SPEED IF YOU LIKE.

11:42.250 --> 11:44.583
WELL...NAH.
THAT WON'T BE NECESSARY.

11:44.667 --> 11:47.583
OKAY.

11:47.667 --> 11:49.583
DR. McANDREW SAID
HE'D BE BY TO TALK TO YOU

11:49.667 --> 11:51.750
AS SOON AS WE GOT
THE NEURO-TEST RESULTS BACK.

11:51.834 --> 11:52.917
YEAH. SOUNDS GOOD.

11:53.000 --> 11:55.917
ALL RIGHTY, THEN.

11:56.000 --> 11:57.792
IS THERE ANYTHING
YOU NEED?

11:57.875 --> 12:02.417
OH, YOU KNOW, I COULD REALLY USE
A PASTRAMI SANDWICH.

12:02.500 --> 12:04.583
AND HOLD THE BREAD.

12:04.667 --> 12:06.792
HEY. HERE WE GO.

12:06.875 --> 12:08.417
LET'S TAKE A PHOTO.
COME ON.

12:08.500 --> 12:09.709
AHA.

12:09.792 --> 12:11.250
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

12:11.333 --> 12:13.083
SEEMS LIKE THERE'S
A LOT OF STEPS INVOLVED

12:13.166 --> 12:14.417
WITH THE CRANE.

12:14.500 --> 12:15.917
ISN'T THERE AN EASIER ANIMAL
WE COULD DO?

12:16.000 --> 12:18.250
NO. CRANES SYMBOLIZE HAPPINESS
AND ETERNAL YOUTH.

12:18.333 --> 12:19.792
YOU KNOW, IN JAPAN,

12:19.875 --> 12:21.250
THEY'RE FABLED TO HAVE
A LIFE-SPAN OF 1,000 YEARS.

12:21.333 --> 12:23.917
OH, WELL, WHEN YOU PUT IT
THAT WAY...

12:24.000 --> 12:25.500
Dash: YO!
GOT THE PROVISIONS.

12:25.583 --> 12:27.250
DIPPED INTO THE CHARLIE FUNDS
A LITTLE BIT,

12:27.333 --> 12:29.166
BUT TOTALLY WORTH IT.

12:29.250 --> 12:31.250
EXCELLENT. PLEASE TELL ME YOU
GOT THE FLAMING CHEESE THINGS.

12:31.333 --> 12:32.875
FLAMING CHEESE THINGS.

12:32.959 --> 12:35.709
YES! THESE ARE THE BEST.
HAVE YOU EVER TRIED THESE?

12:37.500 --> 12:39.750
IT'S ALL GOOD, GUYS.
RIGHT?

12:39.834 --> 12:41.166
RIGHT.

12:41.250 --> 12:42.959
OKAY.

12:43.041 --> 12:45.000
I PROMISE, THEY'RE A LOT LESS
RADIOACTIVE THAN THEY LOOK.

12:48.333 --> 12:49.917
ALL RIGHT, WHAT'S NEXT?

12:50.000 --> 12:51.834
UH, PET STORE.

12:53.959 --> 12:56.542
AND THEN WE SHOW CHARLIE
WHAT DREAMS ARE MADE OF,

12:56.625 --> 12:58.542
JUST LIKE HILARY DUFF
TAUGHT US.

13:01.166 --> 13:02.750
AW, LIKE Y'ALL DIDN'T WATCH
"LIZZIE McGUIRE"

13:02.834 --> 13:04.166
BACK IN THE DAY.

13:13.083 --> 13:16.667
[ NEW AGE MUSIC PLAYS ]
[ SIGHS ]

13:16.750 --> 13:19.000
DON'T THEY HAVE AN APP
TO BE MINDFUL FOR US?

13:19.083 --> 13:22.667
COME ON.
CLOSE YOUR EYES.

13:22.750 --> 13:25.792
CLEAR YOUR MIND
OF EVERYTHING.

13:25.875 --> 13:28.291
JUST OPEN YOURSELF UP
TO THE DARKNESS.

13:28.375 --> 13:29.834
THE LONGER
YOU OPEN YOURSELF UP,

13:29.917 --> 13:31.375
THE WIDER
THE NET YOU CAST

13:31.458 --> 13:34.125
TO CATCH WHATEVER THE UNIVERSE
SENDS YOUR WAY.

13:34.208 --> 13:35.667
THAT'S HOW OPRAH
GOT THE IDEA FOR "O."

13:35.750 --> 13:37.834
LOOK!
IT'S ALREADY WORKING.

13:37.917 --> 13:40.166
QUICK,
DO MORE NOTHING.

13:40.250 --> 13:43.333
Okay. Do nothing.
Do nothing. Do nothing.

13:47.792 --> 13:49.375
OH, MY GOD,
OPRAH IS A GENIUS.

13:49.458 --> 13:51.166
AMEN.

13:51.250 --> 13:53.333
[ MUSIC STOPS ]
WAIT, WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

13:53.417 --> 13:54.625
YOU CAN'T
LEAVE ME ALONE.

13:54.709 --> 13:56.041
THE UNIVERSE
IS SENDING HER TO YOU.

13:56.125 --> 13:58.542
EMBRACE YOUR MINDFULNESS.

14:01.166 --> 14:02.917
HEY,
ARE YOU THE GIRL I SAW

14:03.000 --> 14:05.166
TALKING TO HUNTER
BY THE VENDING MACHINE?
KARA SOUDERS.

14:05.250 --> 14:08.709
I APOLOGIZE IF I SPARKED A RIFF
BETWEEN YOU TWO.

14:08.792 --> 14:11.375
BUT IN MY DEFENSE, I WAS BORN
WITH THIS SLAMMING BOD.

14:11.458 --> 14:13.333
I'M TOO TIRED TO ENGAGE
ON THIS LEVEL, SWEETHEART.

14:13.417 --> 14:14.792
ARE YOU FRIENDS
WITH HUNTER OR NOT?

14:14.875 --> 14:16.834
IF SO,
I-I MAY NEED YOUR HELP.

14:16.917 --> 14:19.166
I BET YOU DO,
BUT I'M NOT MAKING OUT WITH YOU

14:19.250 --> 14:21.000
JUST SO YOU CAN MAKE HUNTER
JEALOUS.

14:21.083 --> 14:23.041
IF HE'S BORED WITH YOUR SEX
LIFE, THAT'S ON YOU, BETTY.

14:23.125 --> 14:26.500
I'M ASHLEY,
HUNTER'S SISTER.

14:26.583 --> 14:29.083
<i>I'LL SAY ONE THING ABOUT KARA.</i>

14:29.166 --> 14:33.500
<i>SHE ALWAYS KNOWS HOW TO MAKE</i>
<i>A TERRIBLE FIRST IMPRESSION.</i>

14:35.625 --> 14:36.709
[ BUNNIES SQUEAKING ]

14:36.792 --> 14:38.583
NO DISRESPECT, MAN,

14:38.667 --> 14:40.834
BUT I JUST DON'T SEE HOW A PET
STORE COULD RUN OUT OF DOGS.

14:40.917 --> 14:43.000
THAT'S LIKE A GAS STATION
RUNNING OUT OF GAS.

14:43.083 --> 14:45.333
SOLD MY LAST CAVACHON
AND CAVAPOO TO TWIN SISTERS

14:45.417 --> 14:47.208
WHO GOT ALL A's
ON THEIR REPORT CARDS.

14:47.291 --> 14:49.083
IT WAS VERY CUTE.
YOU DON'T HAVE ANYTHING?

14:49.166 --> 14:50.542
IT DOESN'T EVEN
HAVE TO BE A PUPPY.

14:50.625 --> 14:52.000
IT COULD BE
ONE OF THOSE GERBILS

14:52.083 --> 14:53.583
THAT RESEMBLE A PURSE POODLE
OR SOMETHING.

14:53.667 --> 14:55.083
MY BOY WON'T KNOW
THE DIFFERENCE.

14:55.166 --> 14:58.542
GIVE ME A SECOND.
LET ME SEE WHAT I CAN DO.

14:58.625 --> 15:01.875
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

15:01.959 --> 15:05.709
MY ABUELA GAVE ME A CHINCHILLA
FOR MY 9th BIRTHDAY.

15:05.792 --> 15:07.709
I NAMED HIM PONCH
AFTER THIS GUY

15:07.792 --> 15:10.375
I SAW IN AN OLD TV SHOW
ABOUT MOTORCYCLE COPS.

15:10.458 --> 15:12.083
UH, THEY'RE PRETTY HARD
TO KEEP AS PETS

15:12.166 --> 15:14.041
'CAUSE THEY WASH THEMSELVES
WITH VOLCANIC ASH.

15:14.125 --> 15:15.208
IT'S CRAZY, RIGHT?

15:15.291 --> 15:17.291
THAT'S INTERESTING.

15:20.000 --> 15:22.750
HERE'S YOUR DAMN PUPPY,
MAN.

15:26.000 --> 15:28.417
THIS IS AN IGUANA.

15:28.500 --> 15:31.041
CLOSE ENOUGH.
LET'S BOUNCE.

15:31.125 --> 15:32.709
Leo: [ SIGHS ]
AND WHERE EXACTLY

15:32.792 --> 15:34.709
ARE WE GONNA GET YOUR
EXOTIC ITEM FROM, DASHIEL?

15:37.333 --> 15:40.250
♪ AIN'T NO SUNSHINE
WHEN SHE'S GONE ♪

15:40.333 --> 15:43.083
♪ AND THIS HOUSE
JUST AIN'T NO HOME ♪

15:43.166 --> 15:47.333
♪ ANYTIME SHE GOES AWAY ♪

15:51.208 --> 15:52.959
[ LAUGHS ]

15:53.041 --> 15:54.959
THAT'S GOOD.
HOW LONG YOU BEEN PLAYING?

15:55.041 --> 15:57.125
OH, MAN. I-I PICKED UP
MY FIRST SIX-STRING --

15:57.208 --> 15:58.417
HEY.

15:58.500 --> 16:01.125
JUST, UH...
JUST CHECKING IN.

16:01.208 --> 16:04.125
UH, YEAH, WE'RE ALL --
WE'RE ALL GOOD. THANKS.

16:04.208 --> 16:05.667
SOME OF CHARLIE'S
TEST RESULTS ARE IN,

16:05.750 --> 16:07.500
IF YOU'D, UH --
IF YOU'D LIKE TO GO OVER THEM.

16:07.583 --> 16:09.875
YEAH, IN A MINUTE.

16:12.667 --> 16:14.500
WHAT KIND OF MUSIC
IS YOUR SON INTO?

16:14.583 --> 16:16.125
HE DIGS
ALL KINDS OF MUSIC.

16:16.208 --> 16:18.417
HE USED TO REALLY BE INTO
THIS SONG BY THE PROCLAIMERS

16:18.500 --> 16:20.583
THAT WE WOULD PLAY FOR HIM
AT BEDTIME.

16:20.667 --> 16:22.083
SORT OF BECAME A STAPLE

16:22.166 --> 16:24.792
IN THE HUTCHISON-FAMILY
DANCE-PARTY MIX.

16:24.875 --> 16:26.917
<i>THOSE WERE SOME GOOD TIMES.</i>

16:27.000 --> 16:28.750
YOU -- YOU WANT TO WALK ME
THROUGH THE CHORDS?

16:28.834 --> 16:30.208
YEAH.
IT'S -- IT'S EASY.

16:30.291 --> 16:33.625
UM, I PLAY IT IN C,
SO IT'S JUST C, F, AND G.

16:33.709 --> 16:35.125
UM...

16:35.208 --> 16:39.125
♪ AND I WOULD WALK
500 MILES ♪

16:39.208 --> 16:42.959
♪ AND I WOULD
WALK 500 MORE ♪

16:43.041 --> 16:44.625
MY BROTHER WASN'T
ALWAYS LIKE THIS --

16:44.709 --> 16:46.959
ALL MAD AT THE WORLD
AND HOPELESS.

16:47.041 --> 16:48.875
HE USED TO BE
AN IDEALIST.

16:48.959 --> 16:51.834
THE DARK KNIGHT WENT THROUGH
A HAPPY GILMORE PHASE?

16:51.917 --> 16:53.333
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

16:53.417 --> 16:56.333
LET ME TELL YOU A STORY
ABOUT HUNTER COLE.

16:56.417 --> 16:59.333
WHEN WE WERE KIDS, HE USED TO
WAKE ME UP EARLY ON WEEKENDS

16:59.417 --> 17:01.125
TO MAKE
CHOCOLATE CHIP PANCAKES.

17:01.208 --> 17:04.333
BUT THE THING ABOUT CHEF HUNTER
WAS THAT HE WOULD RATHER MAKE

17:04.417 --> 17:07.125
ONE [CHUCKLES] GIANT,
PERFECT PANCAKE

17:07.208 --> 17:09.291
THAN 20 AVERAGE ONES

17:09.375 --> 17:11.291
'CAUSE HE ALWAYS HAD TO DO
EVERYTHING BIGGER AND BETTER.

17:11.375 --> 17:13.458
OTHERWISE,
IT WASN'T WORTH DOING.

17:13.542 --> 17:14.917
MY MOMS
WERE THE SAME WAY

17:15.000 --> 17:18.542
WHEN THEY REMODELED
THEIR MASTER BATH.

17:18.625 --> 17:21.041
AND THEN, ONE DAY,

17:21.125 --> 17:23.917
HUNTER COLE JUST KIND OF STOPPED
BEING HUNTER COLE.

17:24.000 --> 17:25.417
HE COULD BARELY
GET OUT OF BED,

17:25.500 --> 17:29.083
EVEN TO MAKE
HIS PERFECT PANCAKE.

17:29.166 --> 17:32.250
THAT'S WHAT LEUKEMIA DOES.
IT ROTS YOU.

17:32.333 --> 17:34.250
WHAT? HE NEVER SAID ANYTHING
ABOUT HAVING CANCER.

17:34.333 --> 17:36.500
I THOUGHT
IT WAS JUST HIS LIVER.

17:36.583 --> 17:38.166
THE CHEMO DRUG
THAT KNOCKED OUT HIS LEUKEMIA

17:38.250 --> 17:40.000
IS WHAT CAUSED
THE CIRRHOSIS.

17:40.083 --> 17:42.500
AND THEN,
AFTER THE TRANSPLANT FAILED...

17:42.583 --> 17:44.667
I JUST...

17:44.750 --> 17:46.875
I CAN'T JUST WATCH MY BROTHER
GO THROUGH THIS, YOU KNOW?

17:46.959 --> 17:51.208
SO I CAME HERE TO DONATE
HALF MY LIVER TO HIM.

17:51.291 --> 17:53.542
YOU CAN DO THAT?
MM-HMM.

17:53.625 --> 17:56.375
OH, MY GOD. YOU'RE LIKE
AN ACTUAL LIFETIME MOVIE.

17:56.458 --> 17:57.709
MM-HMM,
EXCEPT FOR THE PART

17:57.792 --> 17:59.250
WHERE HUNTER
TURNED DOWN MY OFFER.

17:59.333 --> 18:00.667
THAT WAS THAT ARGUMENT
YOU SAW US HAVING.

18:00.750 --> 18:02.417
WHY WOULD HE TURN DOWN
A FREE LIVER?

18:02.500 --> 18:03.834
THAT MAKES ZERO SENSE.

18:03.917 --> 18:05.458
[ SIGHS ] AGREED.

18:05.542 --> 18:07.750
WHICH IS WHY I NEED YOU
TO TALK SOME SENSE INTO HIM.

18:07.834 --> 18:09.208
HE WON'T LISTEN TO ME,

18:09.291 --> 18:11.250
BUT I THOUGHT MAYBE
IF YOU SPOKE TO HIM AND --

18:11.333 --> 18:12.917
WHY, DID HE SAY SOMETHING
ABOUT ME?

18:13.000 --> 18:14.625
HE MAY HAVE MENTIONED YOU
ONCE OR TWICE.

18:14.709 --> 18:18.750
ALTHOUGH, TRUTHFULLY, YOU'RE NOT
REALLY MY BROTHER'S TYPE.

18:18.834 --> 18:20.417
HE DOESN'T USUALLY GO
FOR THE CHEERLEADERS.

18:20.500 --> 18:22.333
HE'S MORE INTO
SKATER-PUNK CHICKS.

18:28.667 --> 18:30.083
NOPE, NOT SO FAST.
I'M A BUSY WOMAN.

18:30.166 --> 18:31.750
WE -- WE NEED TO TALK.
BUSY, BUSY, BUSY.

18:31.834 --> 18:34.083
[ SIGHS ]

18:34.166 --> 18:37.250
HOW LONG DO YOU PLAN ON, UH,
COVERING FOR DR. NADAY?

18:37.333 --> 18:38.625
JUST BALLPARK IT.

18:38.709 --> 18:40.041
JUST BECAUSE
HE'S ECCENTRIC

18:40.125 --> 18:41.709
DOESN'T MEAN
HE ISN'T LEGITIMATE.

18:41.792 --> 18:43.250
MAYBE HIS APPROACH
IS UNORTHODOX

18:43.333 --> 18:45.125
BECAUSE HE'S OPERATING
ON ANOTHER LEVEL.

18:45.208 --> 18:46.834
OF COURSE
YOU'RE GONNA SAY THAT,

18:46.917 --> 18:48.000
BECAUSE YOU STUCK YOUR NECK OUT
TO BRING HIM HERE.

18:48.083 --> 18:49.500
DENA,
THE GUY IS A QUACK.

18:49.583 --> 18:50.875
HE'S BEEN HERE
TWO MINUTES.

18:50.959 --> 18:52.500
WHY ARE YOU ALWAYS
SO QUICK TO JUDGE, ADAM?

18:52.583 --> 18:53.917
[ SCOFFS ]

18:54.000 --> 18:55.917
EVERYTHING INNOVATIVE
LOOKS CRAZY AT FIRST.

18:56.000 --> 18:58.291
I MEAN, PENICILLIN
STARTED AS TRAYS OF MOLD.

18:58.375 --> 19:00.291
ERIN TOOK A BIG RISK
IN BRINGING HIM HERE.

19:00.375 --> 19:02.250
YOU ARE DUSTING YOURSELF
OFF A SUSPENSION.

19:02.333 --> 19:03.875
YOUR JOB IS ON THE LINE,
DENA.

19:03.959 --> 19:05.792
AND YOURS ISN'T, BUT YOU'RE
THE ONLY ONE FREAKING OUT.

19:05.875 --> 19:07.083
WHY IS THAT?

19:07.166 --> 19:08.792
BECAUSE
I WANT TO FIX CHARLIE.

19:08.875 --> 19:10.291
<i>YOU</i> WANT TO FIX CHARLIE.

19:10.375 --> 19:12.125
YOU WON'T LET ANYONE ELSE
HELP YOU.

19:12.208 --> 19:13.959
YOU'VE BEEN DOWN ON THIS GUY
SINCE BEFORE HE EVEN GOT HERE.

19:14.041 --> 19:15.166
ADMIT IT.

19:16.875 --> 19:18.959
SO WHAT?
SO WHAT?

19:19.041 --> 19:21.458
SO, MAYBE IF YOU SPENT
A LITTLE LESS TIME HATING HIM

19:21.542 --> 19:22.959
AND A LOT MORE TIME
TRYING TO FIGURE OUT

19:23.041 --> 19:24.500
WHAT THE HELL HE'S DOING,

19:24.583 --> 19:27.875
MAYBE THE TWO OF YOU
CAN FIX CHARLIE <i>TOGETHER.</i>

19:31.458 --> 19:35.000
[ MOS DEF'S "BEDSTUY PARADE
&amp; FUNERAL MARCH" ]

19:35.083 --> 19:36.208
♪ TURN THE DRUMS UP ♪

19:36.291 --> 19:38.041
♪ HA ♪

19:38.125 --> 19:39.125
♪ HA ♪

19:39.208 --> 19:42.834
♪ HA, HA, HA-HA ♪

19:44.583 --> 19:47.500
♪ HA-AH, AH-AH, HA-HA ♪

19:47.583 --> 19:49.291
Dash:
WE HAVE ARRIVED.

19:49.375 --> 19:51.792
WHAT EXACTLY
IS THE PLAN HERE?

19:51.875 --> 19:53.458
ALLOW ME TO REMIND YOU
OF THE GREAT TEACHER

19:53.542 --> 19:54.917
OF THE EASTSIDE HIGH --

19:55.000 --> 19:56.667
JOE CLARK,
PORTRAYED BY MORGAN FREEMAN

19:56.750 --> 19:58.166
IN THE MOVIE
"LEAN ON ME."

19:58.250 --> 20:00.000
NOW, MR. CLARK
TOOK ARTISTIC LIBERTIES

20:00.083 --> 20:03.000
AND HIRED STRIPPERS TO REWARD
HIS OVERACHIEVING STUDENTS.

20:03.083 --> 20:05.667
HE SACRIFICED HIS INTEGRITY
FOR THE GOOD OF THE STUDENTS.

20:05.750 --> 20:07.458
AS WE WILL DO FOR CHARLIE.

20:07.542 --> 20:09.458
I'M OUT.
THAT'S FAIR.

20:09.542 --> 20:10.834
I NEED TO FIND A RESTROOM
ANYWAYS.

20:10.917 --> 20:13.375
I-I'LL MEET YOU GUYS
BACK AT THE CAR.

20:13.458 --> 20:15.709
GEEZ, LEO, YOUR LEG IS BLEEDING.
ARE YOU OKAY?

20:15.792 --> 20:18.041
YEAH, I'M FINE. IT'S JUST
A BLISTER FROM THE PROSTHETIC.

20:18.125 --> 20:19.875
MY CRUTCHES ARE IN THE CAR
IF IT GETS ANY WORSE.

20:19.959 --> 20:22.250
WE'RE WASTING VALUABLE TIME
HERE, PEOPLE. COME ON.

20:22.333 --> 20:23.792
LET'S GET SOME BOOBS
FOR CHARLIE.
♪ THE ONE
I WANT TO BE CLOSE TO ♪

20:23.875 --> 20:25.875
[ SIGHS ]
♪ BUT I CAN'T TOUCH YOU ♪

20:25.959 --> 20:28.709
♪ 'CAUSE I CAN SEE YOU ♪
TODAY, WE ARE MEN.

20:28.792 --> 20:31.625
♪ WHEN I CAN'T SEE ♪
[ LAUGHS ]

20:34.291 --> 20:36.458
♪ GANGSTER ♪

20:54.542 --> 20:57.959
♪ ZOOM, ZOOM,
THE CLUB KEEPS SPINNING ♪

20:58.041 --> 21:00.000
♪ EVERYWHERE I GO,
YOU KNOW I'M WINNING ♪
NEED TO SEE SOME I.D.s.

21:00.083 --> 21:02.166
MY BROTHER, ALLOW ME
TO INTRODUCE MYSELF.

21:02.250 --> 21:04.500
THEY CALL ME
ABRAHAM LINCOLN.

21:04.583 --> 21:06.625
HERE'S ONE
OF MY BUSINESS CARDS,

21:06.709 --> 21:08.250
JUST IN CASE
YOU NEVER HEARD OF ME.

21:08.333 --> 21:09.375
HOW ABOUT HOOKING ME
AND MY CABINET MEMBERS UP

21:09.458 --> 21:11.000
WITH SOME ENTERTAINMENT?

21:11.083 --> 21:13.208
I'D SAY I NEED TO SEE
YOUR CABINET MEMBERS' I.D.s,

21:13.291 --> 21:16.208
ALONG WITH YOURS,
MR...LINCOLN.

21:16.291 --> 21:18.875
ALL RIGHT, MAN.

21:18.959 --> 21:21.333
COULD I HAVE MY CARD BACK?
I'M RUNNING KIND OF LOW, MAN.

21:21.417 --> 21:22.709
♪ SHE WANT IT,
SHE WANT TO HAVE MY BABY ♪

21:22.792 --> 21:24.125
[ SNAPS FINGERS ]
YOU CAN KEEP IT.

21:24.208 --> 21:25.625
IT'S ALL GOOD.

21:25.709 --> 21:27.458
UH, I'M AN EMANCIPATED MINOR
ONCE THE INK DRIES.

21:27.542 --> 21:30.792
CONGRATULATIONS. BONUS POINTS
ON USING THE WORD "MINOR."

21:30.875 --> 21:32.625
YOU GUYS
ARE NOT GETTING IN HERE.

21:32.709 --> 21:35.834
TIME FOR SOME
C+C MUSIC FACTORY --

21:35.917 --> 21:37.458
CANCER AND CRYING.

21:37.542 --> 21:39.709
YOU KNOW HOW THIS GOES, MAN.
SHOW HIM WHAT YOU GOT.

21:39.792 --> 21:42.041
[ SIGHS ]
ALL RIGHT, HERE'S THE DEAL.

21:42.125 --> 21:46.208
I'M ALSO A MINOR, BUT A MINOR
WHO WON'T SEE ADULTHOOD.

21:46.291 --> 21:48.709
I HAVE OSTEOSARCOMA.

21:48.792 --> 21:52.208
IT IS A RARE CANCER THAT IS
SLOWLY EATING ME ALIVE.

21:52.291 --> 21:54.375
[ SIGHS ]
IT ALREADY GOT MY LEG.

21:54.458 --> 21:56.041
AND THERE'S NOTHING
I CAN DO ABOUT IT,

21:56.125 --> 21:58.375
BUT MAYBE THERE'S SOMETHING
YOU CAN DO ABOUT...

21:58.458 --> 22:00.709
MAKING AN EXCEPTION
TO YOUR MINOR RULE BEFORE...

22:00.792 --> 22:02.750
[ SIGHS ]

22:02.834 --> 22:04.583
...BEFORE THE CANCER
EATS THE REST OF ME.

22:04.667 --> 22:05.875
DON'T CRY, MAN.

22:05.959 --> 22:07.875
I FEEL YOU.

22:07.959 --> 22:09.291
[ SIGHS ]

22:09.375 --> 22:11.417
[ SIGHS ]
I'M PRE-MED OVER AT UCLA.

22:11.500 --> 22:13.750
OSTEOSARCOMA'S
A BRUTAL DISEASE, MAN.

22:13.834 --> 22:15.417
YEAH, YOU KNOW
WHAT I'M GOING THROUGH.

22:15.500 --> 22:17.250
I KNOW THAT YOU'VE
ALREADY LOST YOUR LEG,

22:17.333 --> 22:19.083
WHICH MEANS THERE'S
A PRETTY GOOD CHANCE

22:19.166 --> 22:20.583
THAT THE TUMOR'S
ALREADY GONE.

22:20.667 --> 22:22.125
AND YOUR HAIR'S COMING BACK,

22:22.208 --> 22:24.417
SO YOU'VE CLEARLY ALREADY
COMPLETED CHEMO.

22:24.500 --> 22:26.875
MEDICALLY, I PUT YOUR PROGNOSIS
AT ABOUT 60%,

22:26.959 --> 22:28.375
80% SURVIVAL RATE.

22:28.458 --> 22:32.583
SO I'D SAY ADULTHOOD
IS LOOKING PRETTY SWEET.

22:32.667 --> 22:35.417
HE'S NOT LETTING US IN.

22:35.500 --> 22:36.792
KEEP FIGHTING
THE GOOD FIGHT.

22:36.875 --> 22:38.000
RESPECT.

22:38.083 --> 22:40.041
♪ HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY ♪

22:40.125 --> 22:43.583
♪ MY GOD, MY GOD, MY GOD,
WHAT IS THIS IN MY... ♪

22:43.667 --> 22:45.667
[ NEW YORK DOLLS'
"PERSONALITY CRISIS" PLAYS ]

22:50.500 --> 22:53.542
♪ OH ♪

22:53.625 --> 22:56.250
♪ OOH, OOH, OOH,
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH ♪

22:56.333 --> 22:59.000
♪ GOT A PERSONALITY CRISIS ♪

22:59.083 --> 23:01.834
♪ YOU GOT IT WHILE IT WAS HOT ♪

23:01.917 --> 23:04.917
♪ IT'S ALWAYS HARD TO KNOW
WHEN FRUSTRATION AND HEARTACHE ♪

23:05.000 --> 23:07.417
♪ WHAT YOU GOT ♪

23:07.500 --> 23:12.125
♪ OH, THAT'S WHY THEY TALK
ABOUT PERSONALITY ♪

23:12.208 --> 23:14.333
I COULD WORK WITH THIS.

23:15.667 --> 23:18.333
♪ I THINK WE'RE ALONE NOW ♪

23:18.417 --> 23:21.917
♪ THE BEATING OF OUR HEARTS
IS THE ONLY SOUND ♪

23:24.542 --> 23:27.792
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

23:27.875 --> 23:29.959
OH, DOC, DOC, COME ON.
DON'T KILL THE VIBE.

23:30.041 --> 23:32.291
GRAB SOME MARACAS.
[ LAUGHTER ]

23:32.375 --> 23:33.792
I'M SORRY
FOR INTERRUPTING.

23:33.875 --> 23:35.583
COULD I HAVE
A-A QUICK WORD WITH YOU?

23:36.834 --> 23:38.000
I'LL GET BACK TO MY ROUNDS.

23:38.083 --> 23:39.625
DON'T FORGET
YOUR TAMBOURINE.

23:44.417 --> 23:47.500
SO, I WAS HOPING
THAT WE COULD, YOU KNOW,

23:47.583 --> 23:50.166
TALK ABOUT YOUR APPROACH

23:50.250 --> 23:52.500
NOW THAT YOU'VE HAD TIME
TO EXAMINE THE PATIENT.

23:52.583 --> 23:55.500
OH, WELL, ACTUALLY,
I'M NOT READY TO CONFER.

23:55.583 --> 23:58.375
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU JUST TELL ME
WHAT YOU'RE DOING, THEN?

23:58.458 --> 24:00.041
I MEAN, IT'S NOT
THE BRAIN-STIMULATION TECHNIQUE

24:00.125 --> 24:01.667
THAT YOU'RE KNOWN FOR

24:01.750 --> 24:03.375
BECAUSE YOU HAVEN'T REQUESTED
A-A FUNCTIONAL MRI,

24:03.458 --> 24:06.166
OR ANYTHING TO ASSESS NEURAL
ACTIVITY, FOR THAT MATTER.

24:06.250 --> 24:08.333
I MEAN,
ALL I SEE IN THERE IS, UH...

24:08.417 --> 24:10.583
IS GUITARS
AND TAMBOURINES.

24:12.417 --> 24:14.500
YOU'RE USING
MELODIC-INTONATION THERAPY.

24:14.583 --> 24:17.291
WELL, M.I.T. IS USUALLY
ONLY EFFECTIVE IN PATIENTS

24:17.375 --> 24:19.166
THAT HAVE EXPERIENCED
A STROKE,

24:19.250 --> 24:22.875
AND ACCORDING TO THE TESTS,
CHARLIE HAS NEVER HAD A STROKE,

24:22.959 --> 24:24.375
SO WRONG THEORY.

24:24.458 --> 24:25.709
BUT YOU STILL GET AN "A"
FOR EFFORT.

24:25.792 --> 24:27.709
WAIT A SECOND. LOOK.

24:27.792 --> 24:29.500
I TRIED
TO GIVE YOU A CHANCE,

24:29.583 --> 24:32.208
BUT I REFUSE TO LET CHARLIE'S
PROGRESS BE HELD UP

24:32.291 --> 24:35.375
BY WHATEVER...NEW AGE CRAP
THAT YOU HAVE G--

24:35.458 --> 24:36.750
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
HOLD UP. HOLD UP.

24:36.834 --> 24:38.166
I'M GONNA STOP YOU
RIGHT THERE, DOCTOR.

24:38.250 --> 24:40.542
I REALLY DISLIKE BEING
BOXED IN BY LABELS

24:40.625 --> 24:42.417
UNLESS THEY'RE ONES
I'VE EARNED MYSELF,

24:42.500 --> 24:45.417
SUCH AS A PhD IN BIOMEDICINE,
NEUROSCIENCE FELLOW,

24:45.500 --> 24:47.166
GENIUS GRANT
RECIPIENT.

24:47.250 --> 24:48.750
I COULD GO ON,

24:48.834 --> 24:50.250
BUT I CAN SEE YOUR EYES
STARTING TO GLAZE OVER.

24:50.333 --> 24:52.542
I WASN'T BROUGHT HERE
TO LECTURE ON METHODOLOGY.

24:52.625 --> 24:55.041
I-I-I WAS BROUGHT HERE
TO TRY AND DRAW CHARLIE OUT.

24:55.125 --> 24:57.458
AND IN ORDER TO TAKE ADVANTAGE
OF HIS FORTUITOUS AWAKENING,

24:57.542 --> 24:59.000
I AM MOVING QUICKLY,

24:59.083 --> 25:00.917
BECAUSE IF I DO NOT,
WE RISK LOSING HIM COMPLETELY.

25:01.000 --> 25:03.125
HOW IS WHAT YOU'RE DOING
HELPING HIM AT ALL,

25:03.208 --> 25:04.625
LET ALONE MOVING QUICKLY?

25:04.709 --> 25:06.083
IF YOU OPENED HIS CHARTS,
YOU'D REALIZE

25:06.166 --> 25:08.250
THAT I ORDERED
EVERY SINGLE NEURO TEST

25:08.333 --> 25:10.875
THAT DR. KLEIN WANTED,
SO IF YOU WANT TO ADJUST

25:10.959 --> 25:13.417
HIS TREATMENT,
YOU NEED TO TELL ME THAT NOW.

25:13.500 --> 25:16.709
YOU'RE A BEAUTIFUL MAN,
ADAM.

25:16.792 --> 25:19.083
YOU -- NO, YOU --
YOU REALLY ARE.

25:19.166 --> 25:21.792
BUT CONSCIOUSNESS IS AS FLEETING
AS FIREFLIES IN AUGUST.

25:21.875 --> 25:24.417
THE TIME IT WOULD TAKE
TO EXPLAIN MYSELF TO YOU, IT --

25:24.500 --> 25:27.709
WELL, IT'S TIME BETTER SPENT
WITH OUR PATIENT.

25:38.667 --> 25:43.041
♪ DON'T SHAKE WHEN YOU SEE ME
COMING YOUR WAY ♪

25:43.125 --> 25:45.000
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA,
WHOA! HELP!

25:45.083 --> 25:46.834
WHOA. YOU OKAY?

25:46.917 --> 25:48.583
YEAH, TOTALLY GNAR.

25:50.041 --> 25:51.458
[ Laughing ]
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

25:51.542 --> 25:52.959
WHAT, CAN'T A GIRL SHRED
AROUND HERE

25:53.041 --> 25:54.291
WITHOUT GETTING
A THIRD DEGREE?

25:54.375 --> 25:56.667
YOU MAKING FUN OF ME?

25:56.750 --> 25:58.125
WHAT?

25:58.208 --> 25:59.458
DID ASHLEY TELL YOU
ABOUT EDITH?

25:59.542 --> 26:01.625
EDITH.
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:01.709 --> 26:04.291
YEAH, THAT WOULD BE THE NAME
OF YOUR MANIC PIXIE DREAM GIRL.

26:04.375 --> 26:05.625
[ SCOFFS ]

26:05.709 --> 26:07.792
WAIT!
W-- I'M SORRY, OKAY?

26:07.875 --> 26:09.458
I WAS JUST TRYING TO GET
ON YOUR LEVEL.

26:09.542 --> 26:11.291
I DON'T WANT YOU
ON MY LEVEL.

26:11.375 --> 26:13.959
JUST STAY AWAY
FROM MY FAMILY.

26:14.041 --> 26:16.875
STAY AWAY FROM ME.

26:19.750 --> 26:22.500
"A" FOR EFFORT, GUYS.

26:22.583 --> 26:24.208
AND FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH,

26:24.291 --> 26:26.834
I THINK CHARLIE'S GONNA BE HAPPY
WITH THE OTHER STUFF.

26:26.917 --> 26:29.000
YOU GUYS WANT A HOT DOG?

26:29.083 --> 26:30.458
IT'S ON ME.

26:30.542 --> 26:32.834
WHAT'S GOING ON?
WHERE'S THE STRIPPER?

26:32.917 --> 26:36.208
THAT'S LIKE POURING LEMON JUICE
ON AN OPEN WOUND.

26:36.291 --> 26:39.208
UNFORTUNATELY, WE WERE UNABLE
TO PROCURE A LADY FRIEND

26:39.291 --> 26:40.875
FOR CHARLIE AT THIS TIME.

26:40.959 --> 26:43.166
BUT WE'RE STILL GONNA CELEBRATE
THE SMALL VICTORIES.

26:43.250 --> 26:44.500
YOU CARE TO JOIN US?

26:45.750 --> 26:47.125
YEAH, SURE.

26:48.625 --> 26:50.250
HOLD UP, HOLD UP!

26:51.917 --> 26:53.875
MY CAR!
MY CRUTCHES!

26:53.959 --> 26:55.917
<i>MY IGUANA!</i>

27:07.000 --> 27:08.166
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
I'VE HAD IT.

27:08.250 --> 27:09.417
YOU HAVE TO
GET RID OF HIM.

27:09.500 --> 27:11.083
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
I MEAN NADAY.

27:11.166 --> 27:13.750
I-I HAVE TRIED TO BE RESPECTFUL
BECAUSE I KNOW

27:13.834 --> 27:16.083
WHAT YOU AND DENA WENT THROUGH
TO BRING HIM HERE,

27:16.166 --> 27:17.750
BUT MY INSTINCTS ABOUT HIM
ARE CORRECT,

27:17.834 --> 27:20.083
AND I DON'T CARE
WHAT THIS CRAP SAYS.

27:20.166 --> 27:23.625
HE'S AN ARROGANT CHARLATAN,
AND I WANT HIM GONE.

27:25.125 --> 27:27.083
[ SIGHS ] WHAT?
ARE YOU GONNA CRY?

27:27.166 --> 27:28.917
ARE YOU REALLY GONNA CRY?
NO, I'M NOT -- I'M NOT CRY--
AM I CRYING?

27:29.000 --> 27:30.333
I'M NOT CRYING.

27:30.417 --> 27:34.041
OKAY, LOOK, ERIN,
I'M SORRY, ALL RIGHT?

27:34.125 --> 27:37.041
I-I-I CAME IN HERE HOT,
AND I MADE THIS ABOUT ME.

27:37.125 --> 27:38.583
YEAH.
AND I KNOW
I USED TO DO THAT WITH US.

27:38.667 --> 27:40.208
YOU DID.
OKAY, I'M SORRY.

27:40.291 --> 27:43.208
IF YOU FEEL DIFFERENTLY
ABOUT HIM, THEN --

27:43.291 --> 27:44.709
NO, ACTUALLY, I THINK
THAT YOU'RE CORRECT.

27:44.792 --> 27:46.709
[ Laughing ]
HE'S A DISASTER.

27:46.792 --> 27:48.417
THIS IS A NIGHTMARE.

27:48.500 --> 27:50.083
I-I CANNOT FIND
ONE INSTANCE

27:50.166 --> 27:53.125
OF NADAY PUBLISHING OR LECTURING
IN THE LAST YEAR.

27:53.208 --> 27:54.917
HE HASN'T GIVEN A TED TALK
IN TWO YEARS.

27:55.000 --> 27:56.792
IT'S LIKE HE WAS HELD CAPTIVE
IN A TURKISH PRISON.

27:56.875 --> 27:58.375
OH, MY GOD.

27:58.458 --> 28:00.458
WHAT IF HE WAS HELD CAPTIVE
IN A TURKISH PRISON?

28:00.542 --> 28:03.291
HOW DID
I LET THIS HAPPEN?

28:03.375 --> 28:06.792
B-BECAUSE HE'S A --
HE'S A PhD IN BIOMEDICINE,

28:06.875 --> 28:10.125
HE'S A NEUROSCIENCE FELLOW,
A GENIUS GRANT RECIPIENT.

28:10.208 --> 28:12.959
I-I COULD GO ON,
BUT MY EYES WILL GLAZE OVER.

28:13.041 --> 28:14.625
THAT'S NOT WHY I BROUGHT HIM
HERE, THOUGH.

28:14.709 --> 28:16.375
I WAS GOING
ON MY INSTINCTS --

28:16.458 --> 28:18.375
YOU KNOW, LIKE I WOULD
WITH DOCTORS WITHOUT BORDERS,

28:18.458 --> 28:20.000
WHICH IS FINE
IN SENEGAL,

28:20.083 --> 28:22.792
BUT IT DOES NOT MAKE ME
ADMINISTRATION MATERIAL.

28:22.875 --> 28:25.500
I THINK YOU'RE BEING
A LITTLE HARD ON YOURSELF NOW.

28:25.583 --> 28:28.500
OH, I'M BEING HARD ON MYSELF?
AM I?

28:28.583 --> 28:32.542
BECAUSE ADMINISTRATORS DON'T
BELIEVE IN MIRACLES AND HOPE.

28:32.625 --> 28:34.500
THEY'RE PRACTICAL.

28:34.583 --> 28:38.166
AND THEY DON'T CRY.

28:38.250 --> 28:42.125
WELL, YOU'RE -- YOU'RE ALLOWED
TO CRY AROUND A FRIEND.

28:42.208 --> 28:44.959
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

28:45.041 --> 28:46.709
I THINK YOU MADE
THE RIGHT DECISION.

28:46.792 --> 28:48.333
OH,
NOW YOU'RE DEFENDING HIM?

28:48.417 --> 28:50.500
NO, NO, NO. I'M NOT DEFENDING
HIM. I'M DEFENDING YOU.

28:50.583 --> 28:53.500
YOU DON'T JUST LEAVE FOR A YEAR
AND LOSE OF ALL YOUR SKILLS.

28:53.583 --> 28:54.875
AND IF THAT WERE THE CASE,

28:54.959 --> 28:56.500
YOU WOULD NOT BE
CHIEF OF SURGERY.

28:56.583 --> 28:59.542
[ SIGHS ]

29:05.458 --> 29:06.792
THANK YOU.

29:14.917 --> 29:16.583
SERIOUSLY?

29:16.667 --> 29:18.834
I HAVE SOMETHING TO SAY TO YOU,
AND YOU'RE GOING TO LISTEN.

29:18.917 --> 29:20.500
I DON'T
HAVE MUCH CHOICE,

29:20.583 --> 29:22.875
SEEING AS I'M ATTACHED
TO A DIALYSIS MACHINE.

29:22.959 --> 29:24.709
OR DO I?

29:24.792 --> 29:26.166
YOU KNOW WHAT? NO.

29:26.250 --> 29:29.500
YOU DON'T GET TO CALL
ALL THE SHOTS.

29:29.583 --> 29:32.834
I'VE TRIED MINDFULNESS.
I'VE TRIED HXC SKATING.

29:32.917 --> 29:35.375
AND, YES,
I KNOW "HXC" MEANS "HARDCORE."

29:35.458 --> 29:37.041
AND NO MATTER
WHAT I TRY,

29:37.125 --> 29:39.208
NOTHING SEEMS
TO GET THROUGH TO YOU.

29:39.291 --> 29:42.709
I-I DON'T TRY. PERIOD.
SO I'M DONE.

29:42.792 --> 29:44.709
AND NOT BECAUSE
YOU SAID SO,

29:44.792 --> 29:46.041
BUT BECAUSE
I'M NOT INTO IDIOTS

29:46.125 --> 29:47.834
WHO TURN DOWN
THEIR SISTER'S LIVER.

29:47.917 --> 29:49.542
ARE YOU FINISHED?

29:49.625 --> 29:51.208
ACTUALLY, NO.

29:51.291 --> 29:53.542
IF ANYONE EVEN JOKED
ABOUT GIVING ME THEIR HEART,

29:53.625 --> 29:56.250
I WOULD RIP IT OUT OF THEIR
CHEST WITH MY BARE HANDS.

29:56.333 --> 29:58.125
REJECTING A LIVER
IS AN INSULT

29:58.208 --> 30:00.291
TO EVERYONE
ON THE ORGAN-DONOR LIST.

30:00.375 --> 30:02.542
AND IT DOESN'T
MAKE YOU TOUGH, HUNTER.

30:02.625 --> 30:05.417
IT JUST MAKES YOU A STUBBORN,
SUICIDAL MORON.

30:05.500 --> 30:07.875
NOW I'M FINISHED.

30:09.834 --> 30:12.750
WHEN ASHLEY WAS TELLING YOU ALL
THE JUICY DETAILS OF MY PAST,

30:12.834 --> 30:15.333
DID SHE HAPPEN
TO MENTION JACK?

30:24.000 --> 30:26.041
OKAY. CUTE.

30:26.125 --> 30:28.709
JACK WAS
MY YOUNGER BROTHER.

30:28.792 --> 30:31.166
HE JUMPED FROM OUR ROOF INTO
OUR POOL WHEN NOBODY WAS HOME.

30:32.667 --> 30:35.709
HE WENT INTO A COMA
AND DIED.

30:35.792 --> 30:37.917
THAT'S WHY YOU WERE CRYING
ABOUT CHARLIE.

30:38.000 --> 30:39.917
HE REMINDS YOU
OF YOUR BROTHER.

30:40.000 --> 30:43.125
ONLY HE GOT TO WAKE UP.
MY BROTHER DIDN'T.

30:45.125 --> 30:47.542
WE'RE UNDER
THIS FALSE PRETENSE

30:47.625 --> 30:49.709
THAT WE WON'T EVER GET MORE
THAN WE CAN HANDLE,

30:49.792 --> 30:52.709
THAT PAST TRAGEDIES
WILL SOMEHOW PROTECT US,

30:52.792 --> 30:54.667
BUT IT'S A LIE.

30:54.750 --> 30:58.000
SO WHAT IF ASHLEY DOES
THIS NOBLE THING,

30:58.083 --> 31:00.458
THIS INCREDIBLE,
NOBLE THING,

31:00.542 --> 31:02.792
AND SOMEHOW
IT GOES WRONG?

31:02.875 --> 31:04.375
THAT'S ON ME.

31:04.458 --> 31:06.625
YEAH, BUT ASHLEY SAID
THE SURGERY WOULD BE LOW-RISK.

31:06.709 --> 31:08.959
RISK COMES WITH ODDS.

31:09.041 --> 31:10.375
WHAT WERE THE ODDS
MY BROTHER WOULD HIT HIS HEAD

31:10.458 --> 31:11.917
WHEN NOBODY WAS HOME,

31:12.000 --> 31:15.792
THAT I'D GET LEUKEMIA,
CIRRHOSIS, A BUNK LIVER?

31:15.875 --> 31:17.291
[ SIGHS ]

31:17.375 --> 31:19.000
I'M NOT WILLING TO ROLL
THOSE DICE AGAIN,

31:19.083 --> 31:21.166
NOT ON MY SISTER'S LIFE.

31:21.250 --> 31:24.041
WHAT ABOUT <i>YOUR</i> LIFE, HUNTER?
YOU COULD DIE.

31:24.125 --> 31:26.041
[ SIGHS ]

31:26.125 --> 31:29.333
IF I'M GONNA GAMBLE,
I'D RATHER TAKE MY CHANCES

31:29.417 --> 31:31.834
WAITING FOR
SOMEONE ELSE'S ORGAN.

31:38.291 --> 31:40.375
KARA'S STILL NOT
PICKING UP.

31:40.458 --> 31:41.875
BAIL, MAN.
SHE WOULD HAVE SENT A RIDE

31:41.959 --> 31:43.917
BY NOW IF SHE HAD
GOTTEN YOUR MESSAGES.

31:44.000 --> 31:46.625
GREAT, SO WE HAVE NOTHING FOR
CHARLIE, <i>AND</i> WE'RE STRANDED.

31:46.709 --> 31:48.125
I GUESS WE COULD TAKE
THE BUS.

31:48.208 --> 31:49.625
HOW MUCH MONEY
DO WE HAVE?

31:49.709 --> 31:53.792
Jordi: UH, THREE BUCKS --
ENOUGH FOR TWO OF US.

31:53.875 --> 31:55.500
[ COUGHS ]

31:55.583 --> 31:59.375
DUDE, MY LUNGS ARE ON
"21 JUMP STREET" --

31:59.458 --> 32:01.709
UNDERCOVER AND BOTH
HATING ON EACH OTHER.

32:01.792 --> 32:03.208
I GOT TO GET BACK,
MAN.

32:03.291 --> 32:04.542
OKAY, SO, DO YOU WANT TO GET
THE BUS WITH JORDI,

32:04.625 --> 32:06.083
AND I'LL HEAD BACK
WITH EMMA?

32:06.166 --> 32:07.917
SOUNDS GOOD.
HOW?

32:08.000 --> 32:09.417
YOUR LEG'S BLEEDING, AND YOUR
CRUTCHES WERE IN THE CAR.

32:09.500 --> 32:11.000
IT'S JUST
A LITTLE BLOOD.

32:11.083 --> 32:12.458
I NEED TO BUILD UP MY MY CALLUS,
ANYWAY, SO I'M FINE.

32:12.542 --> 32:14.458
MAN, THAT'S CRAZY.
YOU CAN'T WALK THAT FAR.

32:14.542 --> 32:16.542
LOOK, HE'S RIGHT.
IT'S NOT WORTH YOU GETTING HURT.

32:16.625 --> 32:18.542
ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE HAVING
A GOOD ENOUGH DAY?

32:18.625 --> 32:20.041
YOU KNOW,
I KNOW HOW HARD CHEMO CAN BE.

32:20.125 --> 32:21.417
Jordi: HEY,
DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME.

32:21.500 --> 32:22.917
I GOT ENOUGH STRENGTH
TO GET BACK.

32:23.000 --> 32:24.250
DUDE, LET'S GO, MAN.

32:24.333 --> 32:26.333
ALL RIGHT.

32:50.834 --> 32:53.792
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

32:55.333 --> 32:58.917
I HAVE DECIDED TO MAKE IT WORK
WITH NADAY.

32:59.000 --> 33:00.750
REALLY?
MM-HMM.

33:00.834 --> 33:02.583
DOES THIS MEAN YOU'VE
FIGURED OUT WHAT HE'S DOING?

33:02.667 --> 33:04.583
I DON'T HAVE A FREAKING IDEA
WHAT HE'S DOING.

33:04.667 --> 33:06.917
IS THAT YOUR
PROFESSIONAL OPINION?

33:07.000 --> 33:08.583
WHY THE CHANGE OF HEART?

33:08.667 --> 33:10.583
BECAUSE ERIN'S JOB
IS ON THE LINE,

33:10.667 --> 33:12.959
AND SHE IS
MUCH TOO VALUABLE TO LOSE.

33:13.041 --> 33:14.417
MM-HMM.

33:14.500 --> 33:15.750
PRINCE CHARMING'S
SAVING HIS PRINCESS

33:15.834 --> 33:17.583
AT THE EXPENSE
OF HIS PATIENT?

33:17.667 --> 33:20.917
SO YOU AGREE
THAT NADAY IS WORTHLESS?

33:21.000 --> 33:23.625
I NEVER SAID THAT...
EXACTLY.

33:23.709 --> 33:26.083
I'M JUST SAYING

33:26.166 --> 33:28.458
HE MIGHT BE MORE MOLD
THAN PENICILLIN AFTER ALL.

33:28.542 --> 33:30.125
FOR THE RECORD,
I WOULD NOT LET HIM STAY HERE

33:30.208 --> 33:32.166
IF THERE WAS THE SLIGHTEST
CHANCE HE COULD HARM CHARLIE.

33:32.250 --> 33:33.500
HE'S BASICALLY LIKE A...

33:33.583 --> 33:35.667
A HIGH-PRICED PLAYMATE
FOR THE KID,

33:35.750 --> 33:38.667
AND I'M GONNA CONTINUE
MY COURSE OF TREATMENT
WITH HIS NEURO TEAM.

33:38.750 --> 33:40.667
AND NEXT TIME
YOU TRY TO DISSUADE ME

33:40.750 --> 33:44.291
FROM CALLING IN A SPECIALIST,
I'M GONNA LISTEN.

33:44.375 --> 33:46.792
I DOUBT THAT.

33:46.875 --> 33:49.291
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:49.375 --> 33:53.000
[ SIGHS ]

33:53.083 --> 33:54.500
[ SIGHING ]

33:54.583 --> 33:55.834
SO, HOW DID IT GO?

33:55.917 --> 33:57.417
DO YOU THINK
HE'LL CHANGE HIS MIND?

33:59.000 --> 34:02.250
I DIDN'T CONVINCE YOUR BROTHER
TO HAVE THE TRANSPLANT.

34:02.333 --> 34:05.208
TO BE HONEST WITH YOU,
I BARELY EVEN TRIED.

34:07.834 --> 34:10.750
NICE TO KNOW CHEERLEADERS DON'T
LIVE UP TO THE STEREOTYPE.

34:10.834 --> 34:12.834
YEAH, I DON'T EXPECT YOU
TO UNDERSTAND.

34:12.917 --> 34:14.333
NO!

34:14.417 --> 34:16.500
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND,
OKAY?

34:16.583 --> 34:18.208
IT DOESN'T MATTER
WHAT HUNTER WANTS.

34:18.291 --> 34:20.667
I'M DOING THIS OPERATION
WITH OR WITHOUT HIS PERMISSION.

34:20.750 --> 34:22.583
WELL, THAT'LL ONLY DRIVE HIM
FURTHER AWAY.

34:24.125 --> 34:26.542
LOOK,
WHEN YOU'RE A SICK PERSON,

34:26.625 --> 34:29.333
YOU WANT TO BE SICK
ON YOUR OWN TERMS,

34:29.417 --> 34:32.625
SO YOU TRY TO FIND THINGS
THAT YOU CAN CONTROL.

34:32.709 --> 34:35.458
THIS DECISION IS ONE LAST THING
HUNTER CAN CONTROL.

34:35.542 --> 34:38.959
IT'S NOT MUCH,
BUT IT'S ALL HE'S GOT,

34:39.041 --> 34:40.500
AND I WOULDN'T TAKE THAT
AWAY FROM HIM,

34:40.583 --> 34:44.250
'CAUSE HE MAY NEVER
FORGIVE YOU IF YOU DO.

34:48.875 --> 34:51.208
I'M SORRY.

35:06.041 --> 35:07.625
SO, TODAY WAS FUN.

35:07.709 --> 35:08.959
I GUESS.

35:09.041 --> 35:10.542
CAN I SAY SOMETHING?

35:10.625 --> 35:12.375
I-I KNOW I'M NOT SUPPOSED TO
TALK ABOUT YOU AND LEO,

35:12.458 --> 35:14.208
BUT I JUST WANT TO SAY
I TOTALLY GET IT.

35:14.291 --> 35:15.458
TOTALLY GET WHAT?

35:15.542 --> 35:17.041
I GET WHY YOU CHOSE HIM
OVER ME.

35:17.125 --> 35:18.667
I MEAN, HE'S OBVIOUSLY
A GOOD INFLUENCE ON YOU, SO --

35:18.750 --> 35:19.875
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

35:19.959 --> 35:21.500
OH, NOTHING BAD.

35:21.583 --> 35:23.417
IT'S JUST -- LIKE, YOU'RE EATING
NOW, WHICH IS AWESOME,

35:23.500 --> 35:25.875
AND LEO PROBABLY HAS SOMETHING
TO DO WITH IT, SO --

35:25.959 --> 35:27.375
IT DOESN'T WORK LIKE THAT,
JORDI.

35:27.458 --> 35:31.417
OH. I'M -- I'M SORRY.
HOW DOES IT WORK?

35:31.500 --> 35:33.500
LOOK,
I CAN'T EXPLAIN IT TO YOU.

35:33.583 --> 35:35.000
IT'S JUST IT'S --
IT'S MORE COMPLICATED THAN THAT.

35:37.166 --> 35:38.917
ARE YOU MAD AT ME
OR SOMETHING?

35:39.000 --> 35:40.375
NO. WHY WOULD YOU
THINK THAT?

35:40.458 --> 35:41.875
WELL,
YOU'RE ACTING MAD,

35:41.959 --> 35:43.667
AND YOU'VE BEEN KIND OF WEIRD
AROUND ME ALL DAY.

35:43.750 --> 35:45.375
[ SCOFFS ] WHY DO GUYS ALWAYS
HAVE TO MAKE IT ABOUT THEM?

35:45.458 --> 35:48.500
LOOK,
WE'RE FINE, OKAY?

35:48.583 --> 35:50.500
OKAY.

35:50.583 --> 35:53.041
[ Sighing ] GOOD TALK.

35:53.125 --> 35:55.041
[ GUITAR TUNING ]

35:55.125 --> 35:58.542
Naday: DENA DENA BO BEENA.
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:58.625 --> 36:01.709
I HAVE BEEN LOOKING
FOR YOU.

36:01.792 --> 36:03.500
I GOT SOMETHING
I WANT TO SHOW YOU,

36:03.583 --> 36:04.709
AND I THINK IT'S SOMETHING
YOU'RE GONNA SERIOUSLY DIG.

36:04.792 --> 36:06.208
[ Laughing ]
WELL, I'VE DUG

36:06.291 --> 36:08.375
ALL I CARE TO DIG,
DR. WAVY GRAVY.

36:08.458 --> 36:10.083
IT'S TIME YOU PACK UP
YOUR GUITAR AND HIT THE ROAD.

36:10.166 --> 36:12.542
OH, WHY YOU SO BENT
OUT OF SHAPE?

36:12.625 --> 36:14.333
I'M BENT OUT OF SHAPE

36:14.417 --> 36:16.583
BECAUSE PEOPLE PUT THEIR CAREERS
ON THE LINE TO BRING YOU HERE,

36:16.667 --> 36:18.000
AND THE ONLY THING
YOU'VE ACCOMPLISHED

36:18.083 --> 36:20.041
IS TURNING THIS HOSPITAL
INTO COACHELLA.

36:20.125 --> 36:21.709
WELL, AREN'T YOU
A FUNKY COLD MEDINA?

36:21.792 --> 36:23.709
I HAVE EVERY RIGHT
TO BE ANGRY.

36:23.792 --> 36:27.375
YOU'RE A FRAUD, WHICH
DR. McANDREW KNEW ALL ALONG.

36:27.458 --> 36:30.041
SEE, HE MIGHT NOT HAVE
ALL YOUR FANCY DEGREES,

36:30.125 --> 36:31.750
BUT HE'S 1,000 TIMES
THE DOCTOR YOU ARE.

36:31.834 --> 36:34.417
HE'S BROUGHT CHARLIE
THIS FAR.

36:34.500 --> 36:35.750
HE CAN BRING HIM
THE REST OF THE WAY HOME.

36:35.834 --> 36:37.542
NOT YOU, BUDDY.

36:37.625 --> 36:39.625
WELL, I'M SORRY THAT YOU
AND YOUR STAFF FEEL THAT WAY,

36:39.709 --> 36:41.750
ESPECIALLY WHEN I'VE MADE
SUCH PROGRESS.

36:41.834 --> 36:44.291
[ SCOFFS ] PROGRESS?
YEAH.

36:44.375 --> 36:46.291
NAME ONE THING YOU'VE DONE
TO HELP CHARLIE.

36:46.375 --> 36:48.959
I'D RATHER SHOW YOU.

36:49.041 --> 36:50.375
CAN I?
CAN I SHOW YOU?

36:50.458 --> 36:51.917
COME ON.
COME ON, COME ON, COME ON.

36:52.000 --> 36:53.625
WHEN I WAS ASKED
TO LOOK AT CHARLIE'S FILES,

36:53.709 --> 36:55.291
I READ EVERYTHING
I POSSIBLY COULD,

36:55.375 --> 36:57.500
WHICH IS HOW I FOUND OUT
THAT CHARLIE HUTCHISON

36:57.583 --> 37:00.166
IS AN ONLY CHILD WHO LIVES
IN A SWEET LOS FELIZ APARTMENT

37:00.250 --> 37:03.125
WITH HIS ADORING PARENTS,
NICK AND MANDY HUTCHISON.

37:03.208 --> 37:04.792
I'M FAMILIAR
WITH CHARLIE'S PAST.

37:04.875 --> 37:07.291
Y-YEAH, BUT ARE YOU FAMILIAR
WITH HIS PRESENT?

37:07.375 --> 37:08.750
BECAUSE PRESENTLY,

37:08.834 --> 37:10.959
THAT APARTMENT IS
ONLY OCCUPIED BY MANDY.

37:11.041 --> 37:13.792
NICK MOVED OUT. THEY'VE BEEN
SEPARATED SINCE THE ACCIDENT.

37:13.875 --> 37:15.625
AND WHEN THEY DO TALK,
IT'S MOSTLY TO ARGUE.

37:15.709 --> 37:17.250
[ Chuckling ] YEAH,
I KNOW ALL TOO WELL --

37:17.333 --> 37:20.291
O-O-O-OKAY. OKAY.
THEN YOU SHOULD APPRECIATE THIS.

37:20.375 --> 37:21.792
Nick:
♪ DA-DA-LA-DA ♪

37:21.875 --> 37:23.917
♪ DA-DA-LA-DA ♪
♪ DA-DA-LA-DA ♪

37:24.000 --> 37:25.792
♪ DA-DA-LA-DA ♪
HOW COULD CHARLIE
TRULY FIGHT TO GET BETTER

37:25.875 --> 37:28.333
IF ALL HE HAD TO LOOK FORWARD TO
WAS HOSTILITY AND CONFLICT?

37:28.417 --> 37:30.000
Both: ♪ DA-DA-LA-DA ♪
HE NEEDS TO <i>WANT</i>
TO GET BETTER.

37:30.083 --> 37:31.834
♪ DA-DA-LA-DA ♪
HE NEEDS A REASON.

37:31.917 --> 37:34.375
HE NEEDS HIS FAMILY.

37:34.458 --> 37:35.625
♪ WHEN I GO OUT ♪
♪ WHEN I GO OUT ♪

37:35.709 --> 37:37.000
YOU REALLY THINK
WARM FUZZIES

37:37.083 --> 37:39.333
IS ALL IT'S GONNA TAKE
TO DRAW CHARLIE OUT?

37:39.417 --> 37:41.667
[ SIGHS ]
OH, NO, D-DENA,

37:41.750 --> 37:44.000
HEALING ISN'T
JUST ABOUT MEDICINE.

37:44.083 --> 37:45.834
IT'S ABOUT THE HEART.

37:45.917 --> 37:48.500
NEUROPLASTICITY PROVES
THAT OUR BRAINS

37:48.583 --> 37:51.000
HAVE THE CAPABILITY
TO REWIRE AND REHABILITATE

37:51.083 --> 37:52.625
WITH POSITIVE THINKING.

37:52.709 --> 37:54.667
AND THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT'S HAPPENING NOW.

37:54.750 --> 37:59.000
CHARLIE'S ENTIRE NEURAL SYSTEM
IS BEING REHABILITATED.

37:59.083 --> 38:01.166
LOOK, LOOK,
CHECK OUT THE MONITOR.

38:01.250 --> 38:03.542
♪ AND I WOULD WALK 500 MORE ♪

38:03.625 --> 38:06.542
♪ JUST TO BE THE MAN
WHO WALKED A THOUSAND MILES ♪

38:06.625 --> 38:08.166
YOU CAN STAY.

38:08.250 --> 38:09.542
♪ TO FALL DOWN AT YOUR DOOR ♪
[ LAUGHS ]

38:09.625 --> 38:11.041
I WASN'T GOING ANYWHERE.
MWAH!

38:11.125 --> 38:13.000
♪ DA-DA-LA-DA ♪
[ LAUGHS ]

